KRA intercepted two 20-foot containers loaded with contraband lead batteries at the Port of Mombasa on Wednesday.The content of the containers destined for South Korea had been disguised as 800 bags of Kenyan tea.KRA regional manager Nicholas Kinoti said the government has never issued a license to any scrap metal dealer for the export of used automobile batteries, lead scrap or refined lead.Kinoti said the exporter and the clearing agent will be taken to court before the end of the week.Last Friday, the taxman impounded two Range Rover Sports vehicles imported from the UK and destined for Uganda. The vehicles, valued at Sh24 million, were disguised as household goods.Kinoti said the lost taxes would have amounted to Sh15 million.More on this: Range Rovers passed off as bikes seized